DidaAlliance for Real Change presidential candidate Abduba Dida yesterday dismissed NASA allegations Al Ghurair Printing &amp; Publishing Company tender for ballot papers was tainted.He said NASA presidential candidate Raila Odinga &ldquo;loves teargas and cannot survive three months before looking for a chance to confront the government&rdquo;.&ldquo;I know Raila loves teargas and he can&rsquo;t go three months without it. If he tries, he will be sick,&rdquo; Dida said.He said he did not find anything mischievous in the awarding of the Sh2.5 billion tender.The officials are alleged to have met President Uhuru Kenyatta before the IEBC gave the tender to the Dubai-based firm.&ldquo;When you visit a home [Kenya] you have a right as a visitor to see the father [Uhuru], so that you also feel at home in the new place. It&rsquo;s common knowledge,&rdquo; Dida said on the phone.He said the IEBC demonstrated to all presidential candidates the steps that were taken by the firm to ensure the process was not compromised in favour of Jubilee.&ldquo;It&rsquo;s not bad for Uhuru to meet investors, since they were coming to his country,&rdquo; Dida said.Dida Alliance for Real Change presidential candidate Abduba Dida yesterday dismissed NASA allegations Al Ghurair Printing &amp; Publishing Company tender for ballot papers was tainted.He said NASA presidential candidate Raila Odinga &ldquo;loves teargas and cannot survive three months before looking for a chance to confront the government&rdquo;.&ldquo;I know Raila loves teargas and he can&rsquo;t go three months without it. If he tries, he will be sick,&rdquo; Dida said.He said he did not find anything mischievous in the awarding of the Sh2.5 billion tender.The officials are alleged to have met President Uhuru Kenyatta before the IEBC gave the tender to the Dubai-based firm.&ldquo;When you visit a home [Kenya] you have a right as a visitor to see the father [Uhuru], so that you also feel at home in the new place. It&rsquo;s common